Bill: SF 2483
Article: ARTICLE 1 APPROPRIATIONS
Section: Sec. 3. BOARD OF TRUSTEES OF THE MINNESOTA STATE COLLEGES AND UNIVERSITIES

(1) meet the following hunger-free campus requirements on Minnesota State Colleges and Universities campuses:

(i) maintain an on-campus food pantry or partnership with a local food bank to provide regular, on-campus food distributions;

(ii) provide information to students on the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP), the Minnesota Family Investment Program (MFIP), and other programs that reduce food insecurity;

