The Board of Trustees of the Minnesota State Colleges and Universities must convene a working group to develop policies and procedures to prevent fraudulent enrollment in online courses for the purpose of gaining access to financial aid, campus information technology systems, and student support services. The board must submit a report to the chairs and ranking minority members of the legislative committees with jurisdiction over higher education by January 15, 2026. No additional compensation will be provided for participation in this working group. The working group must include representatives from:

(1) the Minnesota State University Student Association; | (2) the Minnesota State College Student Association; | (3) the Minnesota State College Faculty; | (4) the Inter Faculty Organization;

(5) the Minnesota Association of Professional Employees;

(6) the Minnesota State University Association of Administrative and Service Faculty; and (7) others as deemed necessary by the working group.

